1f1deed9f62d"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Spin, Antisymmetric Exchange, and the Pauli Exclusion Principle\
\>", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812470921170247*^9, 
  3.8124709628884425`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9edd2629-286c-4e27-b611-\
043f34fdcaff"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Wavefunctions and Spin", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124712621964602`*^9, 
  3.812471269177865*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"404a14a2-3c20-414f-927a-\
c91b3055705c"],

Cell["\<\
We stated in our postulates of quantum mechanics that the wavefunction \[Psi] \
should contain all of the information we can know about a system. Although it \
is not explicitly accounted for in the Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger equation, we \
now see that we must include spin in our wavefunction \[Psi]. In the context \
of multielectron atoms or molecules, we usually take spin into account by \
writing our one-electron functions (\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]orbitals\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]) as a product of spatial and spin components,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812470965822681*^9, 3.8124710869668555`*^9}, {
  3.812471117830738*^9, 
  3.812471244790604*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a9c256b2-f4c2-4dcc-96c3-\
ca9f00403570"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Chi]", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], ",", "\[Sigma]"}], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], "\[Alpha]", 
   RowBox[{"(", "\[Sigma]", ")"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124699435472097`*^9, 3.81246994645569*^9}, {
   3.812469990003168*^9, 3.812470001326069*^9}, 3.8124701212743053`*^9, {
   3.8124712940622177`*^9, 3.8124713047393417`*^9}, {3.8124713680214643`*^9, 
   3.8124715054790115`*^9}, 
   3.91770253740528*^9},ExpressionUUID->"d78435d6-0758-4ab7-bee3-\
ff7f73fb82aa"],

Cell["or", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124715125223465`*^9, 
  3.8124715126253176`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4ff074e8-6ff8-4843-bae9-\
706c39fe7bd8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Chi]", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], ",", "\[Sigma]"}], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], "\[Beta]", 
   RowBox[{"(", "\[Sigma]", ")"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124699435472097`*^9, 3.81246994645569*^9}, {
   3.812469990003168*^9, 3.812470001326069*^9}, 3.8124701212743053`*^9, {
   3.8124712940622177`*^9, 3.8124713047393417`*^9}, {3.8124713680214643`*^9, 
   3.8124715249060535`*^9}, 
   3.9177025465912714`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"80cbcacb-b683-4d06-a256-\
42af8c8c5fa3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Note that for any spatial orbital ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Phi]", "(", 
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "359a9c2a-0639-4497-9925-213b6d745aee"],
 ", we can have two possible spin components, \[Alpha] or \[Beta]."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812471527771671*^9, 3.81247158538188*^9}, {
  3.9177025561706486`*^9, 
  3.9177025569155583`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7267dfcc-d5a1-490c-b85f-\
5fe6c718a414"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Particle Labels and the Wavefunction", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812471600028864*^9, 3.8124716819683547`*^9}, {
  3.812617067435463*^9, 
  3.812617069043647*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"bf60e10a-d07a-4e3d-8cb1-\
743d8e195a1f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In the last section, we stated that the wavefunction tells us all of the \
information we can know about a system. However, the wavefunction should also \
be consistent with things that we ",
 StyleBox["can\[CloseCurlyQuote]t",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " know about a system. Quantum mechanics does not give us any way to \
differentiate one electron from another (or any one particle from another \
one), so if we switch the labels we assign to our particles, it shouldn\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]t change the result we would obtain from any experiment. If \
we have an electron in an atom that we call electron 3, and we suddenly start \
calling it electron 1, it makes sense that such a switch in labels shouldn\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]t change any observables."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124716864934807`*^9, 3.8124719125112166`*^9}, {
  3.8124720992482243`*^9, 3.81247210137191*^9}, {3.8126170775027337`*^9, 
  3.812617080814367*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d4d103f7-c2f2-4e93-9b55-\
48074ae80bc3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Remember that the first postulate of quantum mechanics tells us that the \
real information we get from a wavefunction comes from its absolute square, \
with the probability that an object in the state specified by \[Psi](",
 StyleBox["r",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["t ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ") will be found in the volume element ",
 StyleBox["d",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "\[Tau] located at ",
 StyleBox["r",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "at time ",
 StyleBox["t",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "  given by"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812472118983431*^9, 3.812472208669777*^9}, {
  3.8124722689231358`*^9, 3.8124722708768425`*^9}, {3.8124723027374516`*^9, 
  3.8124723028992453`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f515900a-93c0-4a64-b3a5-\
9a346520c98b"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox["\[Psi]", "\[Star]"], 
  RowBox[{"(", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ",", 
    StyleBox["t",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], ")"}], "\[Psi]", 
  RowBox[{"(", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["r",
     FontWeight->"Bold",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ",", 
    StyleBox["t",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["d",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[Tau]"}]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079664251944246`*^9, 3.8079664343142004`*^9}, {
   3.8079689400739555`*^9, 3.8079689680029573`*^9}, {3.807970315263204*^9, 
   3.8079703215316095`*^9}, {3.807970415909548*^9, 3.807970437015459*^9}, {
   3.8079705221296997`*^9, 3.8079705895237727`*^9}, {3.8079740353167067`*^9, 
   3.807974091342613*^9}, {3.8079792460635405`*^9, 3.807979253256398*^9}, {
   3.808056638763859*^9, 3.808056681287653*^9}, 3.808056968998802*^9, {
   3.8080571290891876`*^9, 3.8080571901776743`*^9}, 3.8080573054165645`*^9, {
   3.808062673780108*^9, 
   3.808062685868935*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cb445cdb-13ea-4a33-98cf-\
07e5a385d0de"],

Cell["\<\
This definition indicates that when we switch the labels of our particles \
(usually electrons in our case), the absolute square of the wavefunction \
should not change,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812472310533288*^9, 3.8124723931575313`*^9}, {
  3.8126170968496037`*^9, 
  3.812617102250465*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"50106d27-0f95-4ac4-a2ca-\
5fc27a8b7802"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"|", 
   RowBox[{"\[Psi]", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "3"], ",", "...", ",", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["n",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]]}], ")"}]}], 
   SuperscriptBox["|", "2"]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{"|", 
   RowBox[{"\[Psi]", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "3"], ",", "...", ",", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       StyleBox["n",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]]}], ")"}]}], 
   SuperscriptBox["|", "2"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124724074166007`*^9, 3.8124724113163023`*^9}, {
  3.812472457616372*^9, 
  3.8124725234308033`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0b98fd8c-b27d-47c7-bd5f-\
ae868fec6ec4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "which means that when we switch any labels in our wavefunction, the \
wavefunction can only change by a factor of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", "\[ImaginaryI]\[Phi]"], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"8c470bbe-93f9-4727-b8ab-c9ac578db784"],
 ", where \[Phi] is a phase factor. This requirement can be most easily \
illustrated for the case where there are two particles, as in helium with two \
electrons. We then have"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812472546920706*^9, 3.81247255344049*^9}, {
  3.8124726296116953`*^9, 3.8124726478248205`*^9}, {3.8124726896552534`*^9, 
  3.8124727303688884`*^9}, {3.8124727741646047`*^9, 3.812472775503355*^9}, {
  3.812472884067335*^9, 3.812472912141911*^9}, {3.8124734568705273`*^9, 
  3.8124734568705273`*^9}, {3.8126171107016673`*^9, 
  3.812617124660339*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f746291a-41d6-4459-b81d-\
892450c82565"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"|", 
   RowBox[{"\[Psi]", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]}], ")"}]}], 
   SuperscriptBox["|", "2"]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{"|", 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", "\[ImaginaryI]\[Phi]"], "\[Psi]", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], ",", 
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["r",
        FontWeight->"Bold",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"]}], ")"}]}], 
   SuperscriptBox["|", "2"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124724074166007`*^9, 3.8124724113163023`*^9}, {
   3.812472457616372*^9, 3.8124725234308033`*^9}, {3.8124729281600113`*^9, 
   3.812472996368765*^9}, 
   3.812473459491373*^9},ExpressionUUID->"6dc8eabb-b84b-4964-b52e-\
6070cdd6c29a"],

