  3.8124734966929264`*^9}, {3.9177028104178004`*^9, 3.9177028277521896`*^9}, {
  3.9177028628231063`*^9, 
  3.917702863265917*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5e1e2d5c-1da8-47c1-9999-\
ac9207542cd3"],

Cell["which is only true if ", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124732486136107`*^9, 
  3.812473250976613*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"af3833e6-d33e-4618-9000-\
969a597cefab"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", "\[ImaginaryI]\[Phi]"], 
   SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", "\[ImaginaryI]\[Phi]"]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
    RowBox[{"2", "\[ImaginaryI]\[Phi]"}]], "=", 
   "1"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124724074166007`*^9, 3.8124724113163023`*^9}, {
  3.812472457616372*^9, 3.8124725234308033`*^9}, {3.8124729281600113`*^9, 
  3.812472996368765*^9}, {3.812473186471468*^9, 3.812473209624957*^9}, {
  3.8124732412728014`*^9, 3.812473280586358*^9}, {3.812473501142481*^9, 
  3.8124735066812615`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d2abdfad-add2-4494-9933-\
f80712fa88ed"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This condition is only met if \[Phi] = ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "\[Pi], where ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is an integer. This condition in turn implies that "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124732887441025`*^9, 3.812473291800111*^9}, {
  3.812473322263508*^9, 3.812473349852479*^9}, {3.8124734151417356`*^9, 
  3.812473421938783*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f88d252f-75ce-47e7-b1e3-\
d38b58f2e0d1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", "\[ImaginaryI]\[Phi]"], "=", 
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", "1"}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124724074166007`*^9, 3.8124724113163023`*^9}, {
  3.812472457616372*^9, 3.8124725234308033`*^9}, {3.8124729281600113`*^9, 
  3.812472996368765*^9}, {3.812473186471468*^9, 3.812473209624957*^9}, {
  3.8124732412728014`*^9, 3.812473280586358*^9}, {3.812473501142481*^9, 
  3.8124735263570995`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"43cee6ba-a659-4fa6-8958-\
a67e19e569b2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "So our wavefunction can only change by a factor of \[PlusMinus]1 when we \
switch the labels of two particles. It turns out that particles that yield a \
value of +1 when labels are exchanged are known as bosons, and particles that \
yield a value of \[Minus]1 when labels are exchanged are known as fermions. \
Bosons take on integer values of the spin quantum number ",
 StyleBox["s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", whereas fermions take on half-integer values of ",
 StyleBox["s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". Electrons are fermions (",
 StyleBox["s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox["1", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8fd89cd7-b144-4554-aa59-5ce681c002e7"],
 "), so we\[CloseCurlyQuote]ll mostly be dealing with the case of what we \
call ",
 StyleBox["antisymmetric exchange",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " (exchange of labels changes the wavefunction by a factor of \[Minus]1) as \
we go forward."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812473546248051*^9, 3.8124736691585894`*^9}, {
   3.81247455152393*^9, 3.812474558849125*^9}, 3.812617051279322*^9, {
   3.812617162113443*^9, 3.8126172068413515`*^9}, {3.8126211208820295`*^9, 
   3.812621122913599*^9}, {3.8126225407316437`*^9, 3.8126225974223742`*^9}, 
   3.812623338296956*^9},ExpressionUUID->"31d9e54a-9c97-4549-b37b-\
98858535e3b8"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Sixth Postulate", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8126159553761373`*^9, 
  3.8126159580176225`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ef1b4a7e-7477-4e84-b1df-\
a65bdeeb2d37"],

Cell["\<\
We\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve actually already discussed the antisymmetric exchange \
requirement for electrons, way back in the last postulate of quantum \
mechanics. The postulate is shown again here, as now the terminology will \
make more sense to you.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8126211356194525`*^9, 3.812621194721283*^9}, 
   3.8126234484269357`*^9, {3.917702750327687*^9, 
   3.917702760008586*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"609f8d44-0a6a-403a-97a1-\
6fca0a58074c"],

Cell["\<\
In any system containing a set of identical particles, there is no observable \
that gives information on which particle is being measured. Thus, any labels \
on particles are artificial, and when the coordinates of any two particles \
are exchanged, the absolute square of the wavefunction must not change. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8080673021538053`*^9, 3.808067363108737*^9}, {
  3.80806785555368*^9, 3.808067978308324*^9}, {3.808068010849341*^9, 
  3.808068103205638*^9}, {3.8124737205318413`*^9, 
  3.812473721410514*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7d87add8-0051-4c4d-bd0c-\
eacede16af62"],

Cell["\<\
Therefore, the total wavefunction must be antisymmetric with respect to \
complete exchange of coordinates of any two fermions. Electronic spin must be \
included in these coordinates.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8124737257373767`*^9, 
  3.812473729417974*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"073ef882-2161-4aa4-b3b9-\
8d0ba8aa08a4"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Bosons, Fermions, and Symmetrized Wavefunctions", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812617147961645*^9, 3.8126171542875757`*^9}, {
  3.8126172177958527`*^9, 
  3.8126172215700536`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f0de9bc2-2404-4cf4-be09-\
9e705aa73457"],

Cell["\<\
But what does it mean for a wavefunction to be antisymmetric with respect to \
exchange of coordinates? Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s work through the \
possibilities for a moment, where we are including spin. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81262121307522*^9, 
  3.812621241768715*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d352bc4a-d1b3-4ae2-b73a-\
e8cfe4176f6b"],

Cell["\<\
Remember that we are usually attempting to represent our wavefunction as a \
product of single-particle functions (we are pretty much working only with \
electrons in this class, but let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s use the more general \
terminology of particle for a moment). We write our wavefunction in the form\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812617257792098*^9, 
  3.8126173284119797`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"70a16ab8-628a-43c8-b436-\
df7bdcef9b58"],

