50f7a8a05e27"],

Cell["\<\
We have already used this assumption in the helium atom, for example. For the \
spin component, we are left with four possible arrangements of the spin. The \
first two involve both particles in the same state,\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8126195743751945`*^9, 3.8126196468752513`*^9}, {
  3.8126196946314445`*^9, 3.81261976065292*^9}, {3.812619954696228*^9, 
