   3.812628707123624*^9},ExpressionUUID->"473d7dfa-9928-4c10-addd-\
8a0a40865ce3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "we once again obtain a state that doesn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t change when we \
change the labels of our particles, which fulfills the conditions for bosons \
but not fermions. We\[CloseCurlyQuote]re then left with only one possible \
configuration for our fermions, the ",
 StyleBox["antisymmetric ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "combination,"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.812620665391834*^9, 3.812620687708643*^9}, {
