Cell[TextData[{
 "That is, we can equivalently write our antisymmetrized wavefunction as a \
determinant of a matrix, with each element specifying a possible \
configuration for a given electron label. ",
 StyleBox["The electron label changes with the column, and the electron \
configuration changes with the row",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". This approach works not only for a two-electron case, but for any number \
of electrons! In general, for a system with ",
 StyleBox["N",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " electrons, we can write the normalized, antisymmetrized one-electron \
product wavefunction as"
}], "Text",
