Cell[TextData[{
 "The reason that a Slater determinant works so well for correctly writing an \
antisymmetrized wavefunction comes down to the properties of a determinant. \
If we switch two rows of our Slater determinant, it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \
equivalent to changing the labels on two of our electrons. Remember that \
switching any two rows of a determinant changes the sign, so this property \
fulfills our antisymmetrization requirement. In addition, if we assign any \
two columns to the same orbital ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[Chi]", 
   StyleBox["n",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.810112811439228*^9, 3.8101128248442793`*^9}, {
